Bump react-native from 0.63.3 to 0.64.1 in  custom-sign-in
Issue-body:
Bumps [react-native](https: github.com facebook react-native) from 0.63.3 to 0.64.1.
Release notes< summary>

Sourced from react-native's releases< a>.< em>< p>

v0.64.1< h2>

This patch release is specifically targetted towards fixing iOS build problems in Xcode 12.5. If it doesn't help, please refer to this issue< a>.< p>

Aside from bumping your version from 0.64.0 to 0.64.1, please check your podfile.lock and make sure that Flipper is on 0.75 or higher, and Flipper-Folly is 2.5.3 or higher; if not, add this line to your podfile (or modify it if you already had it):< p> 

use_flipper!('Flipper' => '0.75.1', 'Flipper-Folly' => '2.5.3', 'Flipper-RSocket' => '1.3.1')
< code>< pre>

After which, do all the classic necessary cleans (node_modules, caches, pod folders, etc)(react-native-clean-project< a> is your ally) then do yarn install< code> and a pod install --repo-update< code> (if pod install fails on an error about a Flipper package, just remove the relevant lines from the podfile.lock and run the pod install again).< p>

The only other commit picked & released along the Xcode 12.5 fixes is:< p>

    

  • Update validateBaseUrl to use latest regex (commit< a>) which fixes CVE-2020-1920, GHSL-2020-293.< li>
< ul>

    

    You can participate in the conversation on the status of this release at this issue< a>.< p>

    

    To help you upgrade to this version, you can use the upgrade helper< a> ‚öõÔ∏è< p>

    

    You can find the whole changelog history< a> over at react-native-releases< code>.< p>

    v0.64.0< h2>

    0.64 stable is here üéâ< p>

    Thanks to everyone who contributed and helped to get this together, everyone worked really hard and we hope you are as excited as we are ü§ó< p>

    Some of the most important highlights of this version:< p>

      

    • Hermes opt-in on iOS< li>

    • Inline Requires enabled by default< li>

    • React 17< li>
< ul>

      Among many others - please refer to the blog post< a> for more details.< p>

      

      You can participate in the conversation on the status of this release at this issue< a>.< p>

      

      You can upgrade to this version using the upgrade helper webtool< a> ‚öõÔ∏è
And if you are having trouble, please refer to the new Upgrade Support< a> repository by our awesome community.< p>

      

< blockquote>

      ... (truncated)< p>
< details>

      
Commits< summary>

        

      • 787567a< code>< a> [0.64.1] Bump version numbers< li>

      • cf8a364< code>< a> [local] change post-install to patch RTC-Folly< li>

      • 1c4ac48< code>< a> [local] yarn lock update (?)< li>

      • 76f45d3< code>< a> [local] update RNTester files for 0.64< li>

      • 3912fef< code>< a> Update validateBaseUrl to use latest regex< li>

      • ace025d< code>< a> [0.64.0] Bump version numbers< li>

      • 728d55a< code>< a> Fixing the git attrs for all the people and all the files and all future üôå< li>

      • 8a6ac1f< code>< a> chore: Update React.podspec to require cocoapods >= 1.10.1< li>

      • 138fdbc< code>< a> fix: restore refresh control fix< li>

      • 7f3f80f< code>< a> Fix RefreshControl layout when removed from window (#31024< a>)< li>

      • Additional commits viewable in compare view< a>< li>
< ul>
< details>

Issue-title: isomorphic-webcrypto cannot ensure the security of some operations!
Issue-body:
Hello,

I'm getting this issue while running this app on ios.

[Mon Jun 14 2021 02:43:33.225]  LOG      
    isomorphic-webcrypto cannot ensure the security of some operations!
    Install and configure react-native-securerandom or expo-random
    If managed by Expo, run 'expo install expo-random'
  
[Mon Jun 14 2021 02:43:33.226]  ERROR    Invariant Violation: Native module cannot be null.
[Mon Jun 14 2021 02:43:33.226]  ERROR    Invariant Violation: Module AppRegistry is not a registered callable module (calling runApplication)
[Mon Jun 14 2021 02:43:34.234]  ERROR    Invariant Violation: Module AppRegistry is not a registered callable module (calling runApplication)

Issue-title: e2e tests initialization
Help with -600 Okta Oidc error?
Issue-body:
Hello,

I'm having an issue getting this example to work properly. Upon entering the correct login information, the app throws a error with code -600 (Okta Oidc Error). Looking at the admin logs shows that okta believes a successful login occurred. I have reached the same issue working with both browser sign in and custom sign in. I am using an Android device running Android 10. I read posts in the developer forums that mentioned building a new virtual device solved the problem, but the same error has been thrown on my physical device, and three different virtual devices. 
Has anyone run into this issue and resolved it? It seems very odd that okta reads the interaction as a success, but library receives an error.

Issue-title: Okta browser login page does not appear on Android
Issue-body:
I'm attempting to get `browser-sign-in` working on Android. I've followed the instructions in the README to create a personal Okta account and application, and configure it just as the README specifies.

When I attempt to run the application, on all device configurations I tested, I see the Login button, but tapping it does not bring up the Okta browser login page. Adding some logging statements, the call to `@okta okta-react-native`'s `signIn()` function returns a promise that resolves quickly (no arguments passed to the resolve handler).

This behavior happens on the following configurations I tested:
- Emulator: Pixel C API 28 (Android 9.0, x86)
- Emulator: Pixel 3 API 28 (Android 9.0, x86)
- Hardware device: Galaxy Tab A SM-T510, Android 9

I cloned this repo, ran:

1. `npm install`

1. `cd ios` and then `pod install`
1. `cd .. `

1. open a new terminal window
1. `react-native run-ios`

I get the error:

```
** BUILD FAILED **


The following build commands failed:
	CompileC  src samples-js-react-native browser-sign-in ios build browserSignIn Build Intermediates.noindex Pods.build Debug-iphonesimulator OktaOidc.build Objects-normal x86_64 OIDTokenRequest.o  src samples-js-react-native browser-sign-in ios Pods OktaOidc Okta AppAuth OIDTokenRequest.m normal x86_64 objective-c com.apple.compilers.llvm.clang.1_0.compiler
(1 failure)
```
